comments: Hachimura (LAL) grasps and then quickly releases Jokic's (DEN) jersey as he absorbs the contact in the post, which does not affect Jokic's ability to make his intended pass.
Davis (LAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Reaves (LAL) briefly rests his hand on Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) arm and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Murray (DEN) slightly extends his forearm and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from Reaves (LAL) on the perimeter.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Hachimura (LAL) and Jokic (DEN) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.

Porter Jr. (DEN) moves forward into James (LAL) and initiates contact with his arm/body, which affects his SQBR in transition. A common foul is correctly assessed as the transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as Schroder goes over the pick to maintain his defensive matchup on Murray (DEN).
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Reaves' (LAL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Gordon (DEN) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and gives him a step to avoid the contact.
Murray (DEN) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.

There is no clear or conclusive camera angle to overturn the call on the court of the ball touching Schroder's (LAL) knee last before going out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Nuggets.
Hachimura (LAL) is established in Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs as they briefly engage and immediately disengage while jostling off-ball for position.
Hachimura (LAL) slightly lifts his knee as he engages with Jokic (DEN) and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Jokic's ability to cleanly retrieve the post entry pass.
Davis (LAL) initiates contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm, which affects his play at the basket.

Murray (DEN) makes clean hand on ball contact and dislodges it away from James (LAL) as he dribbles in the lane. Any contact by Jokic (DEN) to James' arm as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Reaves (LAL) commits a take foul on Jokic (DEN).
Gordon (DEN) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Reaves (LAL) brushes Murray's (DEN) elbow and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Murray's SQBR as he begins his dribble up the court.
